	   <tr><td colspan=2>   Ahhh, the magician, a great class. But first things first, High Elves CERTAINLY arent the best race to chose for a mage considering their naturally high WIS. If you want a bunch of mana I would go with an Erudite or a Dark elf. My personal fav is the Dark Elf, that has a nice starting INT(109) that can be maxed out a ton (to 134). But thats all up to you, im a lvl 42 Dark efl mage and doing great. Second, Air and fire pets AREN'T the best at all, I hate the fire pet, and hate the air even more. Fire pets hit hardest, but have so few hit points, but the do cast a small self-buff for about 25 hps. Air just plain sucks, it has the second least hps, although many agi,hits second least hardest, and casts a useless spell that makes it invisible(whats that gonna do? :) Earth has most hps but hits for the for the least amount of dmg and casts a very weak and annoying root spell, thats pretty useless because the pet will keep attacking the monster so it wont be rooted,and is only useful for a mob that likes to run, Water is my favorite, because ithas the second most hps, hits for the second most dmg, casts a nice DD for about 7dmg and goes up over the levels, and it looks REALLY cool:)  but thats just my opinion.<br><br><br>   Hope that helps) <br>mage of the 42nd circle<br>        Xegony<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
